        "---\n",
        "title: \"The Slow Return: Tracking the Recovery of Auckland's Foot Traffic\"\n",
        "subtitle: \"Analysing how Auckland CBD's has recovered from COVID-19 from 2020-2024\"\n",
        "author: \"Georgia Short\"\n",
        "format:\n",
        "  pdf:\n",
        "    toc: false\n",
        "    number-sections: false\n",
        "    geometry: margin=2.5cm\n",
        "---"
      ],
      "id": "fcfa204f"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Auckland CBD has spent the past few years navigating a slow, uneven recovery. Using hourly pedestrian‑sensor data from 2020–2024, I explore how foot traffic changed through lockdowns, reopenings, and the return to “normal”. The goal is simple: understand where the CBD has bounced back — and where recovery is still lagging.\n",
        "\n",
        "I focused on one central question:\n",
        "\n",
        "How has pedestrian activity in Auckland’s CBD changed from 2020 to 2024, and which locations have recovered the most?\n",
        "\n",
        "To answer this, I compared pre‑ and post‑pandemic footfall at both the sensor level (individual streets) and the neighbourhood level (SA2 areas).\n",
        "\n",
        "How do we analyse this change?\n",
        "\n",
        "Using data on pedestrian footfalls collected by Heart of the City and STATS NZ SA2 boundaries over a period of five-years (2020-2024), allowing me to track changes to both temporal and spatial patterns.\n",
        "\n",
        "I first import all packages that will be used and built functions that will be used."
      ],
      "id": "8f352b8d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: True\n",
        "\n",
        "#=========================\n",
        "#     IMPORT PACKAGES\n",
        "#=========================\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import matplotlib.ticker as mtick\n",
        "import requests\n",
        "import time\n",
        "import zipfile\n",
        "import io\n",
        "import geopandas as gpd\n",
        "import folium\n",
        "import branca.colormap as cm\n",
        "\n",
        "#=========================\n",
        "#     BUILD FUNCTIONS\n",
        "#=========================\n",
        "#First function\n",
        "def count_missing(df):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Count missing values in each column of a DataFrame.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Parameters\n",
        "    ----------\n",
        "    df : pandas.DataFrame\n",
        "        The input dataset.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Returns\n",
        "    -------\n",
        "    pandas.Series\n",
        "        Number of missing values per column.\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    return df.isnull().sum()\n",
        "\n",
        "#Second function\n",
        "def footfall_level(count):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Categorise footfall into low, medium, or high levels.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Parameters\n",
        "    ----------\n",
        "    count : int or float\n",
        "        Footfall count for a given observation.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Returns\n",
        "    -------\n",
        "    str\n",
        "        Category label: 'Low', 'Medium', or 'High'.\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    if count < 300:\n",
        "        return \"Low\"\n",
        "    elif count < 1000:\n",
        "        return \"Medium\"\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        return \"High\"\n",
        "\n",
        "#Third function\n",
        "def compute_recovery(df, base_year=\"2020\", compare_year=\"2024\"):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Compute percentage recovery between two years for each sensor or SA2.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Parameters\n",
        "    ----------\n",
        "    df : pandas.DataFrame\n",
        "        Wide-format DataFrame with year columns (e.g., '2020', '2024').\n",
        "    base_year : str\n",
        "        The reference year for comparison.\n",
        "    compare_year : str\n",
        "        The year to compare against the base year.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Returns\n",
        "    -------\n",
        "    pandas.DataFrame\n",
        "        Original DataFrame with an added 'pct_recovery' column.\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    df = df.copy()\n",
        "    df[\"pct_recovery\"] = (\n",
        "        (df[compare_year] - df[base_year]) / df[base_year] * 100\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    return df\n",
        "\n",
        "#=========================\n",
        "#       DATA IMPORT \n",
        "#=========================\n",
        "files = [                   #Assign all csv's to analyise to one name\n",
        "    'akl_ped-2020.csv',\n",
        "    'akl_ped-2021.csv',\n",
        "    'akl_ped-2022.csv',\n",
        "    'akl_ped-2023.csv',\n",
        "    'akl_ped-2024.csv'\n",
        "]\n",
        "df = [pd.read_csv(f) for f in files] #Read csv files into dataframe\n",
        "ped = pd.concat(df, ignore_index=True) #Combine into one datafrane\n",
        "\n",
        "sensor_locations = pd.read_csv(\"akl_ped-Geodata.csv\")"
