        "# Create visualisations of the data \n",
        "First must calculate the number of footfalls per month for year. Created a lineplot to visualise this\n",
        "In Figure 1, we see a dramatic drop in foot traffic in February–April 2020, coinciding with the arrival of COVID‑19 in New Zealand and the rapid escalation to Alert Level 4. The sharp decline reflects the immediate impact of border closures, stay‑at‑home orders, and the near‑complete shutdown of the CBD.\n",
        "\n",
        "Across the following months of 2020, the smaller dips and rises align closely with changes in alert levels, easing brought people back into the city, while each tightening pushed activity down again.\n",
        "\n",
        "Looking at the later years, the pattern becomes clearer. There is recovery, but not back to pre-COVID levels. Both 2023 and 2024 show stronger, more stable monthly activity than during the pandemic, yet they still sit below the pre‑COVID baseline. This suggests that while the CBD is busier than during the pandemic, it hasn’t completely returned to its early-2020 numbers. Likely reflecting ongoing hybrid work patterns, slower tourism recovery, and changes in how people use the city."
